  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-b65f4892e7a0",
  "content": "### Pipeline Steps\n\n## FormatRegistry\n\n```rust\npub struct FormatRegistry {\n    defaults: HashMap<String, Arc<dyn ChunkingStrategy>>,    // kernel-provided\n    overrides: HashMap<String, Arc<dyn ChunkingStrategy>>,   // adapter-provided\n    fallback: Arc<dyn ChunkingStrategy>,\n}\n\nimpl FormatRegistry {\n    pub fn with_defaults(config: &ChunkingConfig) -> Self;\n    pub fn register(&mut self, ext: &str, strategy: Arc<dyn ChunkingStrategy>);\n    pub fn override_default(&mut self, ext: &str, strategy: Arc<dyn ChunkingStrategy>);\n    pub fn resolve(&self, ext: &str) -> Arc<dyn ChunkingStrategy>;\n}\n```\n\nResolution priority: adapter override > adapter register > kernel default > fallback.\n\nKernel ships defaults: MarkdownChunker (.md), ConfigChunker (.toml/.yaml/.yml/.json), PdfChunker (.pdf), FallbackChunker (*).\n\n\n## IngestionAdapter Trait (D69 — Clean Break)\n\n```rust\n#[async_trait]\npub trait IngestionAdapter: Send + Sync {\n    fn domain(&self) -> &str;\n\n    /// Register chunking strategies for formats this adapter handles.\n    fn register_chunking(&self, registry: &mut FormatRegistry);\n\n    /// Return raw source files for the kernel's ChunkingPipeline.\n    async fn ingest_sources(&self, source_path: &str) -> Result<Vec<SourceFile>>;\n}\n```\n\nNo backward-compatible migration — project is pre-release with one adapter. The old `ingest() -> Vec<KnowledgeEntry>` is replaced entirely.\n",
